data.name: customArgsText.ToolTip
data.value: If there is some args that you want to compile with that aren't above, Write them here.

data.name: parenthesesCheck.ToolTip
data.value: If checked, parameters passed in a function must be enclosed in parentheses.

data.name: semiColonCheck.Text
data.value: Lines must end with a semicolon.

data.name: semiColonCheck.ToolTip
data.value: If checked, lines must end with a semi-colon.

data.name: skipLinesUpDown.ToolTip
data.value: Skip count: the number of lines to skip in the input ﬁle before starting to compile; for example, to skip a "header" in the source ﬁle which is not in a valid pawn syntax.

data.name: tabSizeUpDown.ToolTip
data.value: Tab size: the number of space characters to use for a tab character. Without this option, the pawn parser will autodetect the tab.

data.name: optiLevelUpDown.ToolTip
data.value: Optimization level: 0 = no optimizations, 1 = core instructions only, 2 = core & supplemental instructions. Optimization level 1 is compatible with JIT implementations (JIT = “Just In Time” compiler, a high-performance abstract machine).

data.name: debugLevelUpDown.ToolTip
data.value: Debug level: 0 = none, 1 = bounds checking and assertions only, 2 = full symbolic information, 3 = full symbolic information and optimizations disabled (same as the combination -d2 and -O0).

data.name: reportGenDirText.ToolTip
data.value:
Report: enable the creation of the report and optionally set the ﬁlename to which the extracted documentation and a cross-reference report will be written.
Set the path to default to create report in output dir.

data.name: ouputDirText.ToolTip
data.value:
Output ﬁle: set the name and path of the binary output ﬁle.
Set it to null for default.

data.name: includesDirText.ToolTip
data.value:
Include path: set the path where the compiler can ﬁnd the include ﬁles.
Set it to null for default.

data.name: activeDirText.ToolTip
data.value:
Directory: the "active" directory, where the compiler should search for its input ﬁles and store its output ﬁles.
Set it to null for default.
